The probability of drawing two red balls is the product of the probability of drawing a red ball from the first urn and the probability of drawing a red ball from the second urn: $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r + 9}$. The probability of drawing two blue balls is the product of the probability of drawing a blue ball from the first urn and the probability of drawing a blue ball from the second urn: $\frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r + 9}$. The total probability of drawing two balls of the same color is the sum of these two probabilities: $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r + 9} + \frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r + 9}$.

