For carbon-carbon single bonds, $x_0 = 1.53 Å = 1.53 \times 10^{-10} m$, $x = 1.397 Å = 1.397 \times 10^{-10} m$, and $k = 500 \mathrm{~N/m}$. Thus, $E_{\text{single}} = 3 \times \frac{1}{2} \times 500 \times (1.397 \times 10^{-10} - 1.53 \times 10^{-10})^2$.

