## Step 8: Convert the total energy from Joules to $\mathrm{kcal/mol}$.
First, convert Joules to $\mathrm{kcal}$: $1 \mathrm{~J} = \frac{1}{4.184} \mathrm{~kcal}$, so $6.8027 \times 10^{-19} J = \frac{6.8027 \times 10^{-19}}{4.184} \mathrm{~kcal} = 1.626 \times 10^{-19} \mathrm{~kcal}$. Then, to convert to $\mathrm{kcal/mol}$, multiply by Avogadro's number ($6.022 \times 10^{23} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1}$): $1.626 \times 10^{-19} \times 6.022 \times 10^{23} = 97915.72 \mathrm{~kcal/mol}$.

