## Step 2: Recall the relevant probability formulas
The formula for the probability of the union of two events $A$ and $B$ is $P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B)$, and the probability of the complement of $B$ is $P(B') = 1 - P(B)$.

## Step 3: Apply the formula for $P(A \cup B)$ and $P(A \cup B')$
$P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B) = 0.76$ and $P(A \cup B') = P(A) + P(B') - P(A \cap B') = 0.87$.

